Haha where should i start describing my experience with Youlin?
OKOK,.. i start with some boring facts:
He crashed my place for one night before he started his trip throgh France back to Germany. Even though I had little expectations towards this short time (and he also described himself as sometimes a little shy), he managed to convince and surprise me of something different right away.

While my "other" couchsurfer was still there (Hey Danni :D ), Youlin came to my place and after a little chat, we decided going downtown together.

Youlin is a super smart person and open hearted like no other. He lets you participate in his thinking and openly talks about what is on his mind. At some point it even felt for me like i was experiencing my city through a foreigner's eyes, since he pointed out so many things that i did not see or know and shared his thoughts about and like this gave me a completely new perspective on the already known to me Barcelona. 

But not only on sightseing, but also  in private talks, job topics etc. he was a good talker and listener who knows how to keep up a easy going conversation and atmosphere. I totally am impressed by his lifestyle, kindness and "think different"-approach.

In the end we went back to my place and continued our talks with some more beers, before we both went to sleep. If there was something i could bitch around about him: Next time stay a day longer. it was way too much fun having you over!

I wish you a safe trip and a lot of nice experiences on your hitchhike through good old france.  I hope to see you again at some point!

Cheers!

What a great CS experience! Although Youlin was traveling in a different country, we was still able to host me in Hamburg. Incredible! Using his magic, he arranged everything: how to get around, how to meet his roommates and a perfect weather for the weekend! I had a great time in Hamburg and it was mostly thanks to Youlin and his flatmates. Big thanks to all of you!! If you have the chance, see you all in Prague! Vielen Dank!
Youling and his flat mate welcomed us very warmly. It was a pity we were busy all day but in the evenings we enjoyed the talks - and the beer.

Thanks a lot for everything, mate. Hope the apple chutney we left you will be tasty. Tell me, please, what you did with it! (speaking of which - this guys knows a lot about cooking!)

Ulf is a really great host! He was always there to have a good talk and he really knows Hamburg history: we learned a lot! Ours conversations were so fascinating. He offered us diner the night we arrived. Thanks for hosting us! :)

Me and my 2 friends were hosted by Ulf for 1 night. Ulf was realy hospitable and told a lot of interesting stories, made an advice about what we should see in Hamburg and made dinner for us! Thanks a lot for everything!
fromPublicAddressDescription: St Petersburg, St Petersburg, Russian Federation

text: Yeah, Ulf is a great dude with a huge knowledge of the city! He knows all the places whitch are not mentioned in a tourist information books. I couldn't imagine a better host! Absolutely easy going and he made me feel home from the very first moment i entered his flat. Both dumps up. Cheers!

text: Great stay at Ulf's place for 2 nights. Even though he seemed to have much work to do, we got to spend several hours of the first night talking about anything from Hamburg (obviously) to arcane phone technology. Having Ulf telling you about the city's history and local culture is riveting, and it goes beyond a mere exchange of facts and advice. In a way he seems passionate about almost everything and everyone he's encountered, and still craving for more. Mild-mannered, yet unapologetically free-spirited, expressive and lively. Thanks Ulf.

Staying with Ulf was the most interesting coachsurfing experience through the whole Europe trip of ours. I should mentioned that we did not have that much of this experience but to meet Ulf and hear his opinion about food, people, culture, history and Hamburg was really interesting. He told a bit of the city history and later being on City Tour we were laughing how much we already knew thanks to Ulf. So sad that we were so tired after our hitchhiking day and we could not stay longer that night. Its so cool that Ulf host people almost for 5 years.  He is a nice person to stay with! 

Thanks Ulf.  
Ugne & Deimante

Although I spent at Ulfs's place only one night (definietely too short- bad trip planning) , I enjoyed it much! I wish you all the best and much fun "in der geilste Stadt der Welt"!

This was my first Couchsurfing experience and it was awesome. I traveled to Hamburg with my best friend Mar√≠a and we were looking for someone who can host us and hang out with to show us the city and let me tell you that Michael was the greatest! He's so kind and funny! We stayed with him 2 nights and as we arrived at noon, he took our baggage to his office so we can go around the city without carry them, also Michael gave us some tips about what can we visit. 
He make us feel at home since the beginning, also he brought us a copy of his keys. Michael was always flexible about the plans. The first night we were tired, so we ordered pizza and drank wine while we were having very interesting conversations and the second one he tooks us to some bars. 
His personality and sense of humor are the best! Thank for your hospitality Michael and hope we can meet again! :)

My trip was absolutely spontaneous.. But Michael was very friendly and gladly accepted my request. I really enjoyed the stay and time spent with him walking in really nice city Hamburg, talking about travelling experiences and more. Also, Michael is a nice cook too. He even made me some food to go which was very caring gesture. Big thanks for great time and I'm expecting you to come and see Aarhus this year! ‚ò∫Ô∏èüòä

I stayed with Michael 3 nights. 
I have to say that this was my first couchsurfing experience. I never slept before on someones couch. So I had mixed feelings about that. Especially as a girl you are sometimes concerned that the other person could have had second thoughts..
After writing a request on CS he replied in a very nice and decent way that CS sent him my request and that he could host and show me a little bit around after his work. 
So, my first impression on him was that he is a nice, not pushy guy which was the reason why I decided to stay with him. 
And my calm feeling didn't disappoint me, in fact it was quite the opposite. It will not happen very often that someone will impress me with his personality. But exactly that happened when I met Michael.

I arrived with the bus and he picked me up although he had to work. He took my luggage with him into his office and I explored the city since he had to work another 2 hours. We met after his work and went to his apartment where I got my own room, my own keys and got invited to feel like home. Much more that I could have expect. But it was not just that, that made a big impression on me. 
As a social psychologist I am an 'observer'. It is his personality and attitude I am impressed by. From the first time I met him it felt like knowing him for a long time. I appreciate nice, honest, but not boring people, who have interests and passion to share and make you think about stuff. That is how I see Michael. He is a very, very smart and social person with a big heart, who loves to share. He is someone who will always think of others and  doing the right thing. On the other side, he is someone with his own opinion, who will tell you when he is not okay with something. Michael showed me different parts of Hamburg and we had really nice talks. We went in bars but also chilled in his beautiful apartment. 
Because of his smartness without being arrogant I enjoyed every single talk to him. We laughed, had fun, the one or the other drink and just talked about the God and the world. He didn't try to flirt with me or something. So, it was a really comfortable feeling to know that he is nice because it is just his personality. I could write so much more, but I think for now it is enough.
I am still in contact with Michael because I asked him to keep my updated during his big travels, which will start very soon.
Michael: It was a pleasure to meet you. Keep your amazing personality and thanks for making my first couchsurfing experience so unique for  me !!!

Nikhil is a great guy, he cooked for us delicious spicy Indian food! He shows us all the historic center of Hamburg, he teaches me how to make a chai teaüòä, he's really good person, we felt like we know him since a long time, you're so welcome at my home in C√≥rdoba! Take care my friend

text:
I stayed with Nikhil for one night, during my trip to Hamburg for an interview. He had three couchsurfers that day, but still agreed to host me, if I brought along a sleeping bag. 

I had a great time with Nikhil and the other couchsurfers. Although I was very busy during the day, I got to meet Mariana, a Portuguese couchsurfer (another job applicant like me), in the afternoon for a short while, with whom I practiced some Spanish and discussed job applications in Germany. In the evening, we met the other two Swiss couchsurfers, Marie and Aur√©liane in Sternschanze for a beer and I got to learn more about the Swiss culture and had a great conversation with them. Thanks to the other couchsurfers, I definitely had a very intercultural experience during my stay with him, which really interests me.

We also went out to the Reeperbahn with two of his German friends.  

Nikhil is a friendly guy, who really likes to party. In case you want to party in Hamburg, you should definitely consider staying with him.

honestlly, coutchsurfing should give awards for the best host, and I am sure Nik would win them all!! OH MY GOD, how can I describe this amazing person? we instantlly connected and it was like we have met for years :DDDDD Nik is amazingly smart, sweet, respectfull, and veeeeeery funny, we were always laughing and he can make your days bright even when the sun doesn't shine in Hamburg eheheheh (how cheesy, i kow) and I really intend to keep contact with him, I can totally say that I made a friend, hopefully for life!! He is also an AMAZING cooker, he has super funny stories to tell. I came alone to hamburg but I didn't feel alone at all, I had his support whenever I needed, I usually get lost very easily and obviously I forgot my map at his place so he just sent me the directions to my phone with his good will. Nik surely likes to party and knows how to have a good time (you party animal) but he also knows how to have a chill night with some beer on the hand and talk about whatever comes to your mind, always with a huge contagious smile on his face. well, I could stay here all day pointing out the reasons why I simply adored staying with nik, but I think I have made my point, I totally totally totally reccomend this guy, you will love hamburg even more!!

text:
Esther and her flatmate Lena made my short visit to Hamburg a really special one.

As it turned out, Esther was away for the evening so we only communicated through messages. However, she put me in touch with Lena who was an excellent host and very fun company. We caught a concert, visited a new favorite cocktail bar, and admired the spie√üig fashion of the HafenCity dwellers. Lena has a good sense of many different areas of culture, is open, funny, and simply a cool person to hang with! She gave me a good impression of the Hamburg style and taught me some funny German phrases that I will start overusing. 

Esther and Lena's flat is quite gorgeous -- the location is in a peaceful part of the city along a canal, and the apartment is bright, clean, and thoughtfully decorated with touches of style and humor all throughout. I really mean that; even though I didn't meet Esther in person, I can tell from her choice of artwork and super-detailed, self-made Hamburg guidebook that she is a very thoughtful person. I was comfortable there and it was a great place to start the day. Even after leaving, I visited a few places Lena recommended and got my day started on the right track! 

I have visited Hamburg a few times before, but this short visit gave me a new impression of the city. It was great to connect with such positive people, and it made the visit that much more memorable. Thanks, and hope to see you around sometime!

Esther Was an amazing host! She helped me a lot by accepting me to stay! We had some really interesting conversations and her place was ideally located. I really enjoyed my time at hers and it was very clean and cosy. I hope to see you again maybe in London!

Thank you :) 


Adam

Overall it was a really nice experience and I hope to meet her again :)

Esther was such a amazing host, I felt very welcomed and comfortable at her place. Her flatmates were also very kind and fun to hang around with. Wow, that is a lot in 24 hours and that is fun! Tobi is also always curious and open to new experiences and perspectives, it's a pleasure to chat with him over lots of random things in life; while eating late night snacks of bread and cheese -- maybe I am overjoyed with the fantastic food? What do you think, Tobi, haha?
I'm sure we'll see each other again, another time, another place, so until next time, Tobi, take care and enjoy life!
Toby was an awesome guest and he and I are good friends now! Toby is always welcomed here in my home whenever he is ants! üòé

Tobi was a great guest.
Prior to his arrival, he regularly communicated with me, letting me know of his whereabouts and estimated time of arrival; which is greatly appreciated amongst hosts.
In person, Tobi was a genuine traveler: he was opened to experience this sometimes harsh part of Texas and trustworthy of the visitation plans I had for him. He was friendly, open-minded and respectful of my house.
I recommend Tobi to any hosts out there.

Cheers Tobi! Safe travels!

Tobias was a great guest. It was a short one night stay but we got to hang out, went to dinner. Then enjoyed the morning together before he continued his. He is always welcomed here and I would recommend him to anyone.

Tobias is a funny, hilarious and super outgoing person, he can make you smile anytime, we tried so much different foods and I am glad he enjoyed all of it, too bad we missed the actual rodeo, but oh well I had a great time hostingTobi, hopefully to see you in Germany soon üòú

Tobi is a fun guy and a foodie. He's friendly, polite, and it was very easy to hold a conversation with him. His command of English is pretty much perfect, with barely an accent.  He's open minded and tolerant. 

Upon his arrival, we headed out by car so he could take some photographs of the city. Wow, he has a great eye for composition and a good technical command of his camera. Thus, he was able to snap some rich, deeply saturated pictures---including a small lightning strike. Very impressive. Ask to see his photo gallery.

We set out for dinner, and ended up trying  a new place. The service was uneven, but he managed to maintain his composure. Thankfully, the chargrilled appetizers were well worth the wait even if everything else was below average. To make up for the missing shrimp, the next day, we went to a restaurant where I work for a tiny feast. He tried everything, including crawfish. The ladies working there fell in love with him!

Tobi is easy going and easy to talk with. His stay was pleasant but short. Now that I know he's a foodie, I'll plan a proper food tour next time he visits so he doesn't starve again, LOL.  

Every couchsurfer is different. Tobi stands out for having a great personality. HIGHLY RECOMMENDED

Tobias was a great guest. Very polite, tactful and friendly. He was on a busy travel schedule among US cities. I am glad that, beside him getting a much needed sleep at my place, we've also got a chance to have a meal and conversation together. Would definitely host him again!

Tobi was the coolest guy and we had some crazy legendary nights with my other couchsurfers at my house and in Key West!  He is super nice and funny.  You have to host Tobi.  See you in Europe or back in Miami soon I hope!

Tobi was a very nice guest who spent two nights at my place in Asheville. He arrived later than expected, but no problem because he kept in touch and let me know. I think driving on mountain roads through rural NC took longer than he anticipated. He brought a gift of chocolate fudge, so all was well. We stayed up late and had a great conversation. The next day we went to the Biltmore Estate and then downtown for lunch. I worked and Tobi hit the Blue Ridge Parkway in search of waterfalls. Home again for dinner and more conversation. I wish he could have stayed longer, which is about the nicest thing I can say about a couchsurfer. He was off to meet a friend in Charlotte the next morning and resume his trip across America. Check out his blog. Tobi is welcome back any time, and I hope our paths will cross when I visit Europe.
Tobias was a great guest! Even though he was here for one night we had a great time hanging out and share experiences. Is a very easy-going and Charming guy and is welcome in my home anytime
Tobi was a good guy to host. He was chill and easy to work with and all-around cool!

Tobias is such a wonderful guest...if only he could have stayed longer in Savannah. He is upbeat, energetic, has interesting things to say and was just overall a super guest. He was only here one night but we were able to get out on the town and see the sites of the historic district both at night and during the day. Hope you have a great time on your travels Tobi! If you have the chance to host him you won't regret it!
Tobias was a excellent guest. Would have him back anytime; he was able to work around my work schedule and was great conversation too.

When I think of all the reasons people couch surf it's mostly about meeting cool people who want to share their own culture, perspectives, vision for a great future and a better world! Tobi was the epitome of a global citizen!  Fun to be with, open with conversation , courteous, and a fantastic guest.  Do your part, and host this excellent surfer!!

I hosted Tobi for one very short evening. The only regret was not being able to spend more time with him and a longer stay on his part. In the short time we were able to talk, I got the impression he is a great person. He brought me beer upon his arrival. Very kind and polite. Hopefully we can meet up again before your travels end. Safe travels.

I thoroughly enjoyed the experience of hosting Tobi.  We spent way too long talking the evening he arrived, but I enjoyed every minute of it.  I enjoyed hearing about his life in Germany, some of his travels, and his plans for the future.  I can't recommend strongly enough that if he requests a couch in your home, you  should definitely accept!  I wouldn't hesitate to host him again.
A good guest that know what to do and how to behave in all possible situations.

Tobi is such an amazing host!
He really makes you feel confortable and by the end of my days in Hamburg it seemed that I already knew him for a long time. During the days I stayed with him, he was full of activities, but anyway he tried to include me on what he could and also gave me freedom to have my own routine.
We went out together with his friends, he showed me a bit of the city and also gave me lots of explanations and tips about the town.
I really expect that we can meet somewhere again :)

text: This is definately a guys you want to stay with with. Tobi is friendly and super fun to be around. He had bis friends over for pizza saturday night and we all had a great time. My friend Kevin and I were driving through the states on our way back to Canada and requested to stay at Tobias's place at very short notice (day of). He was so flexible and accepted very shortly after my message, giving us plenty of directions too. When we arrived Tobias drove us into town and took us out for good (cheap) food and then awesome cheap drinks, oh and even a trip to a very special bar in Milwaukee over looking the whole city, it was beautiful! text: It was a pleasure to escape from all my duties and deadlines just to host Parth and spend with him nice evening. I hope see you in Hamburg or somewhere else on this planet  and good luck ;)

I stayed with Parth for two nights. He was incredibly friendly and helpful. We communicated via WhatsApp to meet up at his place and went out to eat tasty Turkish falafel and then amazing Indian food. He also prepared a nice, warm chai, which was perfect for this freezing winter. Parth has such a wealth of information concerning living, working, and studying in Hamburg, couchsurfing around Europe, and learning languages. We even talked a bit in Spanish, and his pronunciation is great! Parth is logical and pragmatic with his approach, but he also enjoys relaxing by listening to music and plays the guitar really well. Moreover, we watched a video of a talented sitar player. We talked about Indian culture and cuisine as well India's promising future. He said that I could definitely rest up at home while he was at work since I had injured my left knee while walking in the snow. Overall, I only wish that it had been warmer outside so that we could have explored more of the city together.

I applied for a one night, but my plan had been changed and despite this Parth was able to host me one night more. I am really happy that we met, I like his humor, he is really nice guy. I had a feeling that we had known each other for a very long time. He showed me Hamburg, cooked for me  special Indian food and we went to the party with his cool friends from Indonesia. It was so great!!! Thank you again, hope to see you soon

Parth is kind, easygoing and intelligent person. He is an amazing host! You can talk with him about everything. And it was so fun for me. text:
Nina is a very experimented traveller and a super nice host. I only regret to not have learned more about her trips around the world, because I only stayed one night at her cozy apartment.
We had some drinks, laughs and discussions with a nice friend of her in a bar. And then she showed me around a bit and recommended other good spots in Hamburg.
I wish she can continue exploring the planet from time to time for a looong time!

I stayed one day at Nina's place. She's a friendly open minded girl. She showed me some places in Hamburg I didn't know, we went for a coffee at her friend's home and ate together in a cozy restaurant. I felt very good staying and sharing time with her. You are welcome in Augsburg or wherever I'll be in the future, Nina :) Thank you so much for everything!

I like Nina! :)
She is very very nice. She offered her place for my public trip to Hamburg. After my 16 hours journey with bus, Nina picked me up in bus station, and brought us to her cozy and warm flat. I stayed with another surfer from Linz. Nina hosted both of us. 

We bought some vegetables in Asian Market, then cooked together, and had a very nice dinner. And then she brought us to join a birthday party. It was my best experience ever, being around good heart people in a new city.

I felt so thankful to stay with Nina. Best recommend. I will wait for Nina to come to Indonesia and bring talas chips a lot for her. :) For you too, Philip (another surfer who stayed in Nina's place).

Love you all, guys.
fromPublicAddressDescription: Jakarta, Jakarta Special Capital Region (Java), Indonesia

text: Nina is Awesome! She offered me a place where I can stay. We cooked together and went out with a small group of legendary party people. It was a wonderful evening with magic moments. text: When I was in Hamburg for a conference (as one of the few late 20'ers around), I had to find a lastminute couch due to a storm in the Netherlands, which cancelled my carshare on the day as intended. In the process of finding her place, I met another rower, so what started as a long and disastrous day, ended on a positive note. Meike was quite knowledgeable about design and we had interesting conversations, as we both shared the same philosophy off the "true spirit of couchsurfing" and how this should be treasured. And to respect that, so that people who need a place to crash, can benefit from this. And meeting people, cultures & characters who you otherwise never would. Getting out of your comfortzone. Therefore, it's important to cherish hospitable hosts like Meike. Don't use CS as a cheap/free hotel, but as a way to celebrate the beauty of reprocity (give before you take) and the true kindness in people. It made my day (and world) a little brighter again!

text:
I stayed at Sebastian's place for one night with a friend. He was super keen on showing us the coolest places around and on making us feel at home.  When we finally arrived at his place after having a coupe of drinks together, everything was prepared for us, even though it was a last minute request. 
The next day he spontaniously took us on a sailing trip on his friend's boat and we had a great time. The whole night was filled with jokes, laughter and lots and lots of useful and fun facts about Hamburg, tech, and sailing!

We would always come back for another sailing trip!
If you want to get to know Hamburg from the point of view of a real Hamburger, who knows a lot about the city, and if you want to spend time with someone accomodating, fun and intelligent, I can definately recommend Sebastian as your host and  guide. Thanks a lot!

There are people who show you their city, and there are people who let you live it and make you want to return. Don't recommend you to stay with Sebastian if you are not ready to start planning moving to Hamburg immediately after the trip ;)

I was lucky and very thankful staying with Sebastian - after an annoying car ride he and his girlfriend welcomed me warmly with something to eat and drink. 
And being en route for the Danish coast Sebastian advised me about waterproofing my sailing gear which I am very thankful for.

He is a boy scout, there is nothing to say more! Thanks again!

I had the chance to host Monica and her son Lev  on their last stop of their bicycle holiday. Both are open minded, curious and easy going. We had a long chat late into the night.  She engages in a sensational project caring for kids education and we're still in touch about it.  
I recommend to meet, host or surf with Monica.

Monica and her cute son visited me for two nights during their Ruhr-Area-Tour. They were very friendly and open-minded. And we had some really nice conversations about life.  Monica has great ideas for the education of children and is the founder of the new weekend-school in Hamburg.  I wish you so much luck and fun for your projekts!
Hopefully we see one day again. Have a great time!

It was really nice having Marion and Lev around. Unfortunately we couldn't spend a lot of time together because I had to work. In the evenings we had dinner together and the second night she cooked for us (and it was sooo delicious!) I wish you the best trip and hope to see you again in Hamburg or in Bochum for Urbanatix!

I hosted Monica and Lev at the start of their Ruhrgebiets-cycling-tour. They were both very friendly. She cooked for us and we talked a log time about all and sundry. I wish them many great impressions and less rain for their tour.

The last couple of days I felt blessed with Monica and her son Lev at my place. She was here to make a collaboration with the IMC weekendschool in Amsterdam to introduce this revolutionary school-system in Germany. This school introduces children aged 10 to 14 from disadvantaged neighborhoods and often of migration background to the world of work through passionate professionals acting as volunteers. I really like (to support) people who try to do good to this world and Monica is definately one of them!! Meanwhile her son rediscovered his interest for chess (started at the age of 5) and we played a couple of games. 

They are both really sweet and respectfull. We cooked meals together, had interesting conversations and also did our own things. I could just tell how happy Monica was with her new project. I'm glad I have witnessed the beginning and I wish Monica a lot of strenght and courage to make this project a success.  For sure we'll meet again! Looking forward to it. :-)

I can most definately recommend Monica and Lev to future CS hosts and guests.

It was pleasure having Monica over. She is interested in projects that matter. I am happy to see there are still people around who care for the well-being  of others (teens from families where education wasn't a priority in that specific project, trying to find motivation for those kids to study). I wish you luck with the project that's really something :)

I hosted Monica and her son for one night, They are very polite and easy going people. We had a long chat late into the night. I got a really good insight into the German culture and way of life. I tried converting her son into supporting Bayern Munich and hope i succeeded :) I would recommend to meet her, host her or surf with her if you ever get an opportunity!! Keep in touch and hope to see you in Hamburg someday!!

Florian is a wonderful person, we immediately found out that we have a lot of different themes to talk about. When Florian arrived in Salzburg we went for a short round through the historic part of the city and up to one of our mountains. We spent all the time talking. Of course we had one big theme, our profession, but we also talked about loads and loads of others things. Florian is very well educated and intelligent person, which makes it easy to keep on talking with him for long hours :) 
We went home by electric trolley bus. At home we made some pizza and Christian came back home right before the pizza was ready. Christian found Florian sympathic by first sight and we had a nice chat the three of us. 
In the evening Christian had to go to the fire fighter station and I had to go to sleep because I had to get up at 3.00 am the next morning. So Christian took Florian with him and as far as the "boys" told me they had a lot of fun together until late at night. The next morning unfortunately I could not be at home, but my son very proudly and impressed told me that Florian made the table ready for breakfast and he even took some work from me by taking out the things from the dishwasher. Christian says that Florian is a very reasonable person, a responsible man at work, a good person for long talks and also someone who knows what he wants from life or as breakfast ;) 
Florian is also very respectful, he's careful with things and leaves a place as clean as he found it. 
I definitely do recommend to host him if you get the chance to, Florian is very thankful for all kind of positive couchsurfing-experiences and he welcomes those experiences with a wide opened heart, so if you ever get the chance to host him, don't miss this chance, he's a very special person and you will for sure have a great time when you host him.

It was a pleasure to host Illias and Katharina! They stayed for 2 nights and from the first moment we got along just fine. They both are very interesting people with a lot of cultural experience: yoga, dancing, nutrition... They were extremely kind, always offering to help around the house and sometimes doing it by their own initiative. They were very respectful when I needed to work and very joyful and friendly in our times sharing together. I hope you have a great rest of your trip, and that we can meet again in the future! Remember that you have a place to stay, wherever I am!

Ilias hosted my friend and I for 3 nights, and our only regret is that they passed SO QUICKLY! Immediately we felt welcome and included, and at the same time, free to come and go as we pleased. Ilias is open-minded, friendly and bursting with vitality! He generously shared his time with us, preparing incredible vegan meals and taking us on excursions to secret hidden places we wouldn‚Äôt have otherwise seen without his help. He also gave us both a tango lesson, proving #1 - that I am not unteachable(!), and #2 - his generous heart, to share his skill and time for the love of dance. We exchanged many insights about travel, culture, language, religion, family, health and food under the late night/early morning moon, and no doubt there are more interesting discussions to be had when our paths cross again! Thank you Ilias for your kindness and willingness to invite strangers in -- you made our visit to Hamburg an experience we will never forget!

P.S. You and Jasin are both welcome in Berlin as soon as I have extra sleeping room! Also please give our thanks to Maria for the comfy bed. :) All our best!

text:
It's really a great time. Also it's my first couch surfing, it's a good memory. :-) 
I wrote a lot few days ago!

He is provoking, persistent, and very sarcastic. 

He walked like 5 steps ahead of me all the time as if we were perfect strangers. He was very sarcastic for German custom that I didnt know. Although I hold back my discomfort everytime he said something to me, I finally got very angry for his insulting remark.

When we had a casual Turkish dinner at a chain restaurant, I tried to leave the shop after the meal not knowing that payment should be done AFTER even at the Mcdonald like casual fast food place. (In my country, payment is done BEFORE at such a fast food place. Also, people can get a kind of slip that reminds them payment isnt done yet at restaurants.) Then, he stopped me saying, "Hey, you need to pay for your stuff." and I did. Later, he went on " You can get foods for free in Japan, huh?" in a very ironic tone. I finally reached my limit of patience and told him stop being sarcastic bout something I didnt know here thats very annoying.  He insisted he is perfectly right in every aspects and enjoy being sarcastic thats his style. 

I felt extremely disgusted and stopped talking to him completely and left his place in the early morning, which is clear sign of NO to him. Before leaving his place I blocked him all apps that we had contacted that also clearly shows my discomfort being with him.

 I simply wanted to forget this and move on as a traveler with limited time, yet when I figured he wrote me a reference I need to bother myself to write him back tho I didnt want to spare any negative energy anymore as Ive had enough with him.

Back to Belgium I feel enriched by our encounter and Hamburg has definitely won a special place in my heart forever.

It was my very first time traveling alone to far-away continent, so apart from excitement to see beautiful old historical buildings and stunning scenery, I also had lots of worries and insecurities. So as soon as we both were back in Hamburg, we met to talk about our trips and now we are going on a trip together. On purpose this time ;-)

If anyone still has doubts: Yes, I would definitely recommend him, as host, as surfer, as friend.
I really connected with Andre as we had a few things in common during interesting conversation. We shared some German wine and dinner.I would be happy to stay with him or host him again.

Andre is not only an attentive host, he is really interested in getting to know his guests. Dear couchsurfer, if you get to hear Andi's opinion towards CS or the world, feel lucky and enjoy. For our talks, I got the impression he is someone who actually lives his convictions. He is really open, empathic and also funny. 
One curious thing, is the fact that wherever Andre travels, he tastes the food. He saves the taste in his mind and he brings it back to his home through his culinary skills. I was quite impressed after he cooked a typical Mexican breakfast. 
Espero vernos pronto Andre, un abrazo!

Andre is such a friendly guy. You cannot miss all of his stories traveling and living life! He treated me really good as his guest and we had the time to have really good conversations, breakfast and some beers of course. I was lucky during my stay in Hamburg because they were some beautiful fireworks and a street festival which we enjoyed together with his friends.
I strongly recomend him! Thank you so much Andi!

I had a great time staying with Andre in Hamburg. He is very knowledgeable, and he strives to create a great experience for the guest. We also got to chat about our respective travel experiences, which was great. I would definitely recommend staying with him!

Staying with Andre for two nights was my first CS experience ever. Therefore I was a bit nervous before I arrived at his apartment. But Andre's welcoming and friendly nature and his very clean apartment made me feel comfortable from the first to the last minute of my stay. On both nights we had some great conversations. I enjoyed listening to the many stories he experienced while travelling and his open-minded attitude to many other topics. Andre gave me some good advice which places to visit on my first day in Hamburg. On the second day he prepared a nice breakfast we enjoyed together. After that I was grateful that he showed me a place called "Treppenviertel" at the river Elbe. In the end I was actually a little bit sad to leave after "just" two wonderful days. I would be pleased to visit Andre again. 
You can consider yourself as very lucky if you get the chance to stay with him or even have him as a guest!
Thank you, Andre! Enjoy your time in South America, I wish you all the best.

text:
I had a great time with Olga and her family. Nice medium sized apartment with everything necessary for a traveler. Very green and placid area. In close vicinity a subway station with U-1 that'll get you to city center in 40-50 mins.  
Material things aside - the individuals of this family are absolutely amazing! Both Olga and her husband are highly skilled professionals, mature and well-rounded people. The younger family member is smart and adorable boy on his way to becoming the same as his parents :) Olga, who'd traveled all over the world and seen many remote corners of this world, has (relatively) recently went off on a new adventurous journey - being a mother :) And she does so with all her kindness and hard-working approach. Her husband is also a unique man with an extraordinary skill set, including, but not limited to, excellent story telling, giving great advice, creative furniture design and production. 
Recommend Olga's place to travelers who are not into late night time out (as I am!), as it was inconvenience for her! Sorry about that.
Olga Is very kind and friendly. If she invites you to play the card game memory you¬¥ll never win. Thank for everything, Olga.

We met Olga in a tiny cute village in Germany and as the place was magical Olga and her friends were so as well! 
Thank you for the walks, the apples, the talks, and the fun in the evening!

text: We spent a nice night in Lisa's house. Her family is amazing, they're very friendly people, it was a pleasure for us to talk and for my child to play too! text:

David is one of those people that you always want to find, but rarely do! Hees a 100%er, something that his extensive CS experience also confirms. Hees a trustfull guy that i now would call a friend. Hees the perfect surfer and has alot of good storries and brain power :)
See ya!
It was nice to meet David and to spend a weekend with him. He is an experienced traveler and have a lot of stories to tell. I will be happy to meet up again.

David is just great! Fun to hangout with. Easy going. We have alot of intressting convertions! Even i only met him twice it feels like we have known eachother for a long time... if you have the chance to get to know David, u should take it! üòâüëå

Words can't describe David as a guest and even less as a person.
To me, David is not my guest. He is family. He is my brother.

Me and David's history startet a couple of years back when I stayed in David's home during my trip through Central America.
Certain events early on in our friendship meant we got very close in a short amount of time.

As a guest, you can expect David to be helpful, giving and very respectful. David is a great guy to hang out with, and if you do, you are guaranteed a good time in the best company you can imagine.

David is also not the kind of Couchsurfer that expects you to keep him entertained - he is more than able to keep himself busy, which especially is very nice when you have a packed working schedule and arrive home late and tired.

My girlfriend and I enjoyed sharing our home with David, and he can consider our home his home anytime.

We hope to see you again soon, hermano.

Best wishes, love and recommendations,
Mads & Camilla

I have met David before, but this was my first time hosting him. David is using couchsurfing for all the right reasons. He's looking for friends and not free nights. What I really like about David's company is his way of being himself. He never changes, he always sticks to his own opinion - I respect that. He's always keen on stricking up an insteresting convesation, which can go in any possible (and impossible) direction.
David has on multiple occasions told me, that he's looking for that 3% of couchsurfers that are really worth the trouble of finding new hosts/surfers. What I'm sure he hasn't realized yet, is that he's most definitely self-included in those 3%. 

If you're looking for more than a couch or a quick reference, this is the guy you wanna meet up with.

Second time I host this great latino gentleman. Couchsurfing brought us together and we became good friends. This is truly what couchsurfing should be like every time. David is simply awesome! Always up for fun & jokes and happy to share experiences and adventures from his own life. 

I now know that I will always have a second home and a real brother in Honduras. See you soon again hermano!

Lasse

David is a good storyteller, and with his hosting experience you will always have something interesting to hear. He enjoys socializing and prefers people to sightseeing in every case. Would it be a huge party or an evening with friends in a pub, he's up to it. He even invited me to the local couchsurfing party and we‚Äôve met a lot or wonderful people there. We shared a lot of stories about our countries, professions and CS friends :)

It was fun and easy to host him. David is a nice guest, tidy and careful. He is a good cook, too. He cooked a national dish for us, and it was tasty and filling.

I am sure we will meet again :)

Cool dude.
Was down to chill from the start.
Took him to the springs and the rest was history.
I would host him anytime.

Dave came to my place and it didn't took me long to realize that we are going to get along like super good.

text: David David...! I have had an incredible time with Mister David for the past 2 days. We went along with each other quite well, straight from the beginning. Trust me, this guy has got endless remarkable CouchSurfing stories to tell you about. On top of that, I have rarely encountered such a generous open-minded person in my life. His numerous travel experiences has made him who he is today. Thank you David, I have learned a lot from you.

Before agreeing to host David, I read some of his references which are all positive. I came to find out why this is the case. 
David is an extremely nice person, who is easy going and will make you laugh a lot. As a guest he is very respectful and aware of the fact that he is in your home and not his own. His eagerness to help out underlined his appreciation. Furthermore he has a lot of great stories about CS himself that he is willing to share.
He was my first experience with CS and I am happy that was the case. He showed me what this is all about. Helping people out, becoming friends with strangers.
I would host him again any time, and I think you should do the same, if you get the chance to!

No, I'm not kidding :) He is awesome! Hope to see you again bro! :)

Well this dude is awesome. David made my stay in Honduras, half of good emotions belongs to him. Time we'd spent together is a reminder for me of how important is to catch the right vibe and how easy everything can be after that.
The place is great, David is doing his best to decorate it well, to make it look more like himself - fancy! Hahaha))
Love this man, definitely wait for you hermano in Moscow to share vodka and my balalaika with you

David, as an ambassador of CS, obviously had a bunch of crazy stories happened while hosting - and he was willing to share! Some of them surprise, some make you laugh, but the way of telling them is marvelous.
The main thing - David was very hospitable and flexible - he leaved a key in a spot when he had to leave before me and another his guest got back; and send the picture of a spot of course :)
Also, he drew a sketch of me and another guest, shared with us food, movies, conversations!
Besides facts - it was a great stay, I'm amused how David still has so much eage to help and comfort guests after all these hundreds people he hosted so far :)
Hope my pasta did it to your reference for me, man! :)

David was great! Not only was he sharing his home and his food with me but also he helped me out more than once. He waited for me at the airport to pick me up ad when I tried to get to Copan Ruinas he not only offered to drop me a the bus station but also waited with me for hours as I didn't know that on good friday buses had a differend schedule( or no schedule at all). I didn't manage to get on a bus to Copan so he took me to his place again and offered me to stay one more night. He is a great host, fun outgoing and pacient with his couchsurfers. Thank you so much for everything David!

David is a heart that pumps vividly coloured stories that leave you in awe... in fact he's sure got more colours than the electromagnetic spectrum. Dave is a symphony with multiple passionate movements, ones that bring you joy, indestructible childish joy, ones darker that challenge you and trouble you, ones that taunt you way out of your comfort zone, ones that enlighten you and make you reflect upon the world, under all       angles and non-angles, there are no rules! Dave in itself is a gorgeous, complex organic reasoned  piece of human harmony. And gotta stress the word human because few are as humane as him and with a sharp and tackling sense of morality that generates enormous respect from me. It is absolutely crazy, in a bit more than 72 hours you unveiled to me parts of myself that I didn't realize! Do you know what that does to a person?? You sure do. 

His mind is like another planet. He's     f*cking cosmic   !!!

David was a fantastic host,  he did our washing for us,  drove us the the mountain to hike, took us to get food. We played some pool with him at his place as well which was fun. He also had really good advice about places to go in Honduras. We was very welcoming and we felt very comfortable around him. 
One of the bests hosts that we have had.  Such an awesome guy. 
Cheers David, it was such a pleasure.
This dude be my real homie-g, ya hear?

text: Great vibe, great guy, definite recommended stay!

Davidsito is a really great member of the CS community. So incredibly helpful and alot of fun, (and might I add a super talented and inspiring photographer!)

Even though I was super annoying with my exhaustive, relentless questioning, david eventually set my (and my mom's) mind at rest about visiting Honduras when I was about to skip the whole of Central America due to irrational bad reputations posted all over the internet...

We travelled together to an incredible microbrewery (d&d) nestled in the jungle close to lake yojoa and visited the epic pulhapanzak waterfall. He recommended so many amazing places, including the utila bay island water cay where I spent a few days which was a real highlight of my entire trip! 

Honduras feels uncommercialised compared to its neighbouring countries, the people are super friendly, in the main no one will try to constantly sell you things or rip you off, food is super tasty and the landscape is uniquely beautiful and largely untouched.

David is a really friendly person and always wanted to help , he brought me to  a really good dentist the husband of his sister.. and i joined him on making some pictures for his work in a small town , really nice..And we went out in the weekend ! ( yea he likes RUM )  thanks for everything amigo!

Well what can I say about David, the easiest way would be to call him a great Friend! I only stayed 3 nights with him but starting at the beginning I felt like we knew each other for a long time. He is a great host, who cares more about the comfort of the couchsurfers than about his own. Rum and pool is always a great option!, you might even find a Pinocchio at his place. He is a fantastic photographer and person. I am already looking forward to seeing him either back in SPS or Vienna:)

David welcomed me and my friend to his home in San Pedro Sula, we had a little change of plans due to the transportation situation from El Salvador to San Pedro Sula, and we showed up two days later, regardless of that he welcomed us to his home. He is a true artist and I had so much fun looking at his works and also his studio! Although we didnt have time to shoot together but I hope one day we get to create art together! Hope to see you again in Europe or Asia or elsewhere in the world! :)

Una gran brava persona, molto gentile ed  estroverso. Sono stato due notti abbiamo.cucinato Italiano e altro cibo di differenti.culture , √® una persona molto simpatica e ospitale, lo raccomanderei a tutti.grazias david
David is a very welcoming and compreensive individual, thinking about other people's needs. He helped us planning our trip and managing our time left so we will stay as source of inspiration.

Great great host. Do no miss to meet this amazing guy. Funny, smart, very helpful. He even picked me up ob tje bus terminal and we drank quite a bit of good rum together, haha. I had wonderful time with him in San Pedro Sula a he gave many tips where to go in Honduras. It's always great to meet a person with such positive attitude and love for life as David. Thank you very much for your hospitality and I hope to see you again in Europe or anywhere else in the world. Cheers!

David offered me to host me when I wanted to go to another city.
So I changed my plans to know him. It was the best decision ever ! 
That guy is awesome, very flexible and generous.
He's a true photo artist and has a lot to teach !
He's very friendly and you'll feel at home with him. A lot of interestings conversations and sharings !
Man I'll be waiting for you in brasil !! Now we are friend !!
Have a nice trip !! 
See you

Dave is kind, funny and an awesome host, super knowledgeable and friendly. He really cares about his country and knows about the best places not only in San Pedro, but all of HONDURAS! Anybody would would be beyond blessed to be hosted by this guy. Visiting Honduras is a must!  Thank you Dave!

Dave Diaz - Legend! I owe this guy so much honestly and really look forward to team up in Europe and travel somewhere together üòã this is a little update on the first reference I wrote: after returning to San Pedro Sula Dave took me out for a road trip to the puhlapanzak waterfall and we stayed in a brewery in midst the jungle where we got wasted for my b-day üòÖ it was incredible with humming birds and lovely company of other travelers, back in SPS I got to meet another guest of Dave - really interesting guy üòä we made a photo shooting (my first one!) and I got introduced to photography by David - was able to take pictures of a baptism and assist in another shooting at an amazing hacienda near the Copan ruins! üòâ you made San Pedro Sula the heart of Honduras for me!

David embodies everything that is Couchsurfing.  I think we were his first guests with a baby and he went out of his way to make sure we were comfortable.  From the moment we arrived until the moment we left David made us feel like family and went above and beyond to show us hospitality.  We also had the privilege of meeting his beautiful and generous family.  We cannot thank David enough for our unforgettable experience and only hope that we can repay the kindness when he visits us in Canada.  With love.

I stayed his house 3 nights. He is a super friendly and hospitality. We talked a lot about photography and Honduras. He was little bit busy but it was good experience. His house super clean and comfortable. I hope next time we can spend more time and make a photoshoot. Salud :)

Hmm... What to say of such a unique couchsurfing experience I had with David?

I would start by saying: Dont go there if you're a jerk, you just dont deserve it! But that would be putting to much shadow on the picture.

I felt so lucky to be hosted by David since the first moment. Actually the second, when we went to eat baleadas, after I had entered an other car by accident and threw my backpack inside it hahaha.

To connect like this with somebody in a country that I visit give all the raison d'etre to this website. 

I had my first job as a professional photograph, that I very enjoyed, when we went to a wedding he was scheduled for. That took me so out of my comfort zone!
 Thanks for sharing me your clothes and your passions!

The day after, we did a photoshoot and I profoundly enjoyed the experience. I think we got very close that day, hermano. 

This is only 2 big lines but I could write so much more because it is all the rest that made this CS an unforgetable expericence. 

Ill keep it short, THANKS BRO! 

This guy is awesome!!

I hope you get more of this 10% of cs that worth it, like you said in your profile. Mostly, I wish you make tons of good friends in the weeks coming.

text:
Does David really need more references? If he ever asks you for a couch SAY YES. I think he's hosted near 100 people and surfed only twice. Through hosting he's had valuables stolen, computers destroyed, and bathrooms destroyed with stink...but it doesn't seem to stop him for a minute! I guess there's a reason he's the ambassador of San Pedro Sula, Honduras...he's a straight badass! 
I probably should have hung out with him longer, just got to know him over a 24 hr period. He waited at the bus stop for me an extra hour for my delayed bus? He gave me a HUGE bed instead of a couch? He fed me way too much chicken fingers FO FREE?? This was more of couchluxurycruising than couchsurfing heh...
Awesome guy, great pad, and a big friendly contagious smile!

text: I've known David long enough (and well enough) to forget that I was actually Couchsurfing--it felt more like visiting a lifetime amigo. Even still, I owe a reference! My time in San Pedro Sula (indeed in Honduras) was based solely on meeting Dave. Long talks...photo sessions...book browsing...a few much-needed photoshop lessons...helado (to celebrate being cavity free :D...peliculas & an incredibly entertaining live theatre Latin version of 'The Wizard of Oz' which I will never forget (vamos ya camino :). Good times with a great friend: precisely what I needed. I enjoyed my quiet respite from the rigors of the road...from Baleadas to home-cooked meals (gracias por tu mama tambien ;). Talented. Trustworthy. Loyal. Dave is the kind of friend you hope to never lose. One thousand "thank yous" for your wonderful hospitality and a dozen apologies for all the onions & vegetables ;). Gracias por todo! Abrazos hermano.

Yasir's stay with me could not have been more timely, only a few days before my first ever trip to Pakistan was about to commence. Getting caught up in conversation about Pakistan, as well as a myriad of other topics, we spent half a day just sitting and talking on my balcony, until the searing afternoon summer heat finally drove us inside. Yasir's style of communication is indeed candid and direct, which I found very refreshing. There are a lot of interesting topics I would have still liked to touch upon. I hope the opportunity will present itself before long!

It was a great pleasure to host Yasir and even greater pleasure to talk to him.  As a Pakistani who is deeply knowlegable about European history, religion and culture from books as well as living,  working and travelling in Europe for several years, he is the right person to go for an insight for an "outer" view of cultural differences of East (Asia) and West (Europe), as well as less tangible differences among  EU cultures.

As an open minded and gentle persol he is an ideal companion for talk about life and its nuances. And by the way, he can cook a tasty Pakistani food for you :-)

We hosted Yasir only for one night and we are sad that we didn't have more time together. He is an optimistic, flexible and polite person, and we enjoyed our converstions very much. You won't be disappointed in case you will be hosting him. Yasir, hopefully we will meet again!

Special mention goes out to his skilled use of the spices I've been reserving in my kitchen cupboard for just the right meal. Yasir is welcome back at Casa Aguiar anytime!

We talked about very interesting things, deep things. Yasir, you are so friendly and so pleasant, thank you so much for those two days, OBRIGADO!
Our last hour together was eating a tasty (and spicy!) dinner that Yasir have cooked, a dish from Pakistan! Was a wonderful food, a thousand thank you!

I wish next time you can stay in my home with my family :) You'll be very very welcome here. Return whenever you want and spend the time you want.

text:

I'm still extremely thankful for this because at that moment I had a rough period and I still can't imagine a better place to stay at that time than with Yasir and Giulia. 

Despite the fact that Yasir had a lot of work for school he showed me around and made sure I had things to do and wasn‚Äôt feeling alone at any time. We had long, open and deep conversations and I‚Äôm still grateful for this. He made me see things from other perspectives and this was exactly what I needed. Yasir was very nice, he responded to my public trip and invited me at his place in Hamburg, I definitely recommend him, he as so so much travel experience and can give the best trips to visit Hamburg, we also had some very nice conversations about love, Pakistan, travel, Couchsurfing... Yasir offered me first with a comfy bed. Shared room was nice for sharing our endless stories related to our travel, religeon and Politics which are sensitive but very interesting to get other perspective. And he tried to recommand good tips as a route customised for a walking tourist like me to look around the city. Hope you to keep surfing your journey while settling your life in your country. Catch you later. Vielen Dank.

For a long time I was hoping to meet this fine young fellow again and I finally made it to visit him in Hamburg. That was a bit hard because we're both like to hit the road quite often but once we managed it, it was absolutly easy going. Yasir cares about his guest a lot and will call you a few times just to make sure you'll reach the right spot to meet him. Like everytime, we spend a lot of time having interesting conversation while having breakfast, dinner or just a pleasant walk through a park. Well, Yasir is the kind of guy you'll have interesting talks with all along the day and night. His open minded and thoughtful attitude makes it a great experience to exchange about cultur, travelling, well let's say everything... I mean it!
He is also a considerate cook and his hot and delicious meals made me kind of cry just one time!!! He also offers a diverse collection of tea of which especially one sounds a bit weird but all of them taste magnificent! It has been a pleasure to spend some time with him and I'm excited to see where we will meet next time.
So staying, hosting or even just meeting him will give you numerous impressions and I bet boredom won't be one of them :)

We spent together two lovely days. And it wasn't for the first time :) Yasir is a person who you want to come back to. Whenever you meet him, you can rely on him and spend interesting time. He is someone who you can set deep and strong connection with. Recommended!

Thank you, Yasir!

Yasir is amazing and kind person. He is very experienced about travelling. I really liked having a conversation with him. We didnt have enough time to  together( i was extremely tired) but he showed around to me. Thanks for his hospitality and kindness üòä

text: My stay with Yasir was fantastic. He's an intellectual and very friendly person who can talk about anything! Speaking with him was honestly better than walking around Hamburg... I was around good people, good discussion and good feelings--what more could you ask for. We met up in the city, had stimulating conversations and ate delicious food. Ultimately he provided an authentic couchsurfing experience: one that helped me see the city and that gave me a friend I wouldn't have met otherwise. Very highly recommended! :D

If you're a motivated, exploring soul, passionate about questioning and deep discussions, you will definitely find the company of Yasir a very special memory to remain. He's one of those charged personalities, that light up any room or discussion with their presence. Moreover, he's an excellent cook and has so much to share of his travel experiences and gathered stories from different corners or the world. One definitely leaves his household a little bit richer inside. Inthank Yasir for his warm invite and the comfortable stay I had at his place. He took really good care of me and the other staying couchsurfer, even though it was a last-minute request. Thank you again! Hope our paths will cross one day again!

Great kumpir and conversation. Thanks!

text:
Yasir was my first proper CS host. And there's a lot of things I have to thank him for: great conversations that also gave me loads to think about and interesting perspectives, really good food that I'll try to imitate now that I'm back home, but more importantly important tips, lessons and opinions on travelling and couchsurfing, which will accompany me along my future paths. 

Yasir himself is very intelligent, knowledgable, but most of all humble and respectful towards all people, beliefs and ideas. And if everybody had even half his sense of social responsibility, the world would surely change into a better place.

text:
Thank you Yasir for the great experience in PADOVA!!!

Yasir and his friends Safiq, Shelbi and Naim hosted Mathias and me for one night in their all-Pakistani flat in Padova...
Our short trip to Padova started bad (it was raining cats and dogs)...but immediately got better when we entered their home :) We were served great Pakistani food and wonderful Chai...and we got a crash-course in Pakistani culture: music, strange utube vids,and (my favourite) PLAYING CARDS :D 
Before going to sleep we were listening to stories about snakes and ghosts and we were offered an insight into the Pakistani look onto this world...
And last but not least, Yasir did a sightseeing trip through Padova with us...and shared all his knowledge about this beautiful city with us...

Thanks again for being such a great host and for sharing home, food and knowledge with us :)

text:
Iris is very hospitable,optimistic,talkative and she is beautiful with happy big smile always! I contacted with her before my trip,and I was so lucky to be her CSer cause she didn't host people so often in the past.

She gave me advice about my trip in Germany and I did accept and change my plan.She told me where to take a cheaper transportation and finally I saved money too.

She even tried to help me to arrange my stay when she knew I would visit Berlin.
She is easygoing and she didn't mind I arrived late so I got much more time to visit Berlin before heading to Hamburg.

She shared her travel experience and her life with me.I have to say she is very cosmopolite,ambitious and independent! You will feel she is a powerful traveller and enjoy her story!!
Her apartment is very nice and cosy.Those little stuff and photo album showed that she is such an interesting person!

She took me to a famous restaurant to have fantastic breakfast the next day.And yes I was awkward when using knife and fork :-p
She accompanied me to visit Hamburg with Free Walk, and took me to funny and interesting places later on.
I knew a lot from her explanation and finally I tried two can-not-miss things in Germany --beer and sausage!!!

Thanks Iris,for giving me such incredible and happy experience in Hamburg,I had a great time with you to finish my very first journey out of China!! Highly recommend!  :)

text:
Hamburg ‚Äì wow, what a beautiful city! I stayed with Iris over the weekend, she (being a perfect host) showed me everything I needed to know for my sightseeing tour, which I really enjoyed. But then, after she got off from work, she turned it up a notch, first we had some beers and a very tasty burger in the "Schanzenviertel", then went to her friends birthday party, pre-drinking and getting to know new people, afterwards going to the "Reeperbahn", partying and dancing, and for the Afterhour she even showed me the typical fishmarket on sunday morning.
Danke, Iris, you made my stay in Hamburg so very awesome and unforgetable!

Iris is really a nice person! She's chatty, interesting and fun. We spend a day cycling through Hamburg, where she showed me the harbour, and went to a Oktoberfest party at the top of a shopping mall. Awesome day, with a great host! :D

text:
Mike was an amazing host! So helpful and always giving with an open hand. We spent 2 days together and although we didn't have much time together the time we had was spent watching a Norwegian tv series that he would translate for me. 
His generosity is beautiful! From helping Another Couchsurfer that needed a place and he couldn't accommodate her he instead bought her dinner! To dropping me at the pier on the day I left. So lovely! I had a great time and I would recommend if you are visiting Koh Toa drop him a message and if he's free he will show you secrets of Koh Toa :) Thankyou Mike I had a blast

Mike is a really super cool guy, also nice, helpful and generous. I spent a great time with him. He stayed with me the evening and he showed me good places in Koh Tao.
Thanks again for your hospitality :)
You was a super couchsurfer. It was nice to meeting you.

All the food I tried with Mike was to die for. Always budget concious yet good quality food. He gave me a lift to and from the pier which was really nice of him! 
He was laidback and didn't mind me coming and going as I liked. 
Thanks again!

Mike hosted me for 2 nights during my stay in Koh Tao and I couldn't have asked for a better host!  Even if he had to work during my stay,he managed to spend the evenings with me, having delicious food in beautiful  locations, introducing me to his amazing friends on the island and sharing some of his impressive travel experiences with me. He's a passionate traveller and a real foodie! It's impossible to eat bad food while staying with him. Finally I had the perfect last night having cookies and beer while watching a movie! 
All in all a great, very laid-back guy, easy to talk to and fun to spend time with.You're always welcome to Berlin Mike! :)

Me and my friend needed a place to sleep for a couple days in Koh Tao. Mike didn't just host us but also showed us around and made us feel home and welcomed. He offered himself to drive us to the pier one by one at 5 am, which we will always be grateful for.

We really enjoyed hanging out with him and would definetely repeat this experience. 

Keep in touch! X

text: This is the second time hosting Dilan, and just like the first time it was pleasure to host her and have her around. It is always fun to hang out around Dilan, she has a unique sense of humor. I would chose to host Dilan in a blink of an eye.

Dilan! Dilan! Dilan! I had the pleasure of meeting and hosting Dilan through a mutual friend of ours Jess ‚Äî whom I hosted prior to hosting Dilan! Dilan was really flexible and really engaged in our little quirky community. She was such a breath of fresh German air for a few days. I really enjoyed our mini deep convos early in the morning with fancy cans of draft lattes. 

If you host her you are guaranteed to have some good chuckles, deep convos and a fun and real person to hang with. I would gladly host Dilan over and over again. 

Thanks for blessing us with your presence Dilan! You‚Äôre amazing! 

Xx
Both Dilan and Jessica were great guests, they were both great to be around and talk with. I would host them again anytime.
Dilan & her friend were very polite & organic with their flexible, constantly flowing and adventurous schedule. Safe travels! :)
Had an excellent time and made a great friend.
These two were great guests.  I would host them again anytime
Dilan and her friend were lovely to host. They were friendly and flexible with their arrival time.

Dylan is a fun friendly seasoned  traveller, unfortunately I had to go work on my boat so we didn't get much time to hang out but her short stay was a pleasure and i feel perfectly at ease have her in my home. and can certainly recommend her.

I hosted Dilan and her friend Jessica for 3 nights. They were flexible, friendly, and fun to host. Dilan is uncomplicated and easy to get along with :) We cooked dinners, we went out, we watched movies, and had fun times. I would host Dilan and her friend again at any time.

Salva has been a cool and reliable host. He is happy to meet new people and make their stay in Toulouse nice.
He can recommend trendy restaurants and bars, but also historical and monumental sights.
He is also keen to hang out so if you are feeling like doing something fun during your stay just let him know!
Joaquin stayed 2 nights at my place. He was a gentle and generally nice guest. Thanks a lot for your visit!
La mejor referencia para Joaquin. Es una persona inteligente con la cual puedes hablar de muchos temas y con mucho sentido del humor. Espero el destino nos vuelva a cruzar. Abrazo enorme!
Joaquin, eres una persona muy amigable y sociable,  fue muy agradable tu visita por  mi casa en Brasil. Que  gustazo conocerte y espero verte de nuevo en Chile.
Nice chap! Definitely very clean and was highly flexible. We dint get much time to hang out but perhaps that awaits my return trip to Germany. Good luck with your masters, Ashwin.

text:

Recommend him c:

text:
Sheela is a kind and thoughtful person. She let me stay in her room for 3 nights which was a bit to long as there was not much space and no privacy which i thought was a problem for her as she told me i was the first to stay that long.
You also need to take the train into the city so i didn't venture into doing that the whole time i was there so just hung around a small area where she lives. She works part time at burger king in the evenings at the weekend but she was ok with me staying at her home while she was out. And as a bonus she brought me home burgers so a big thanks for that as well as the curry she cooked me.
I would recommend staying with her.
Sheena was really nice, she prepared me some Indian specialities. It was really cool to meet sheena, she is a really kind person.

I stayed at Sheelas place for just one night. I arrived late because one of my trains got delayed. I also had to get up early to catch a flight, but Sheela didn't mind at all. She was so kind, funny and nice to talk with. Very open minded and thoughtful.  We had so much to talk about, especially we talked a lot about traveling. I definitely recommend staying with Sheela! üòÉ

Sheela is such a lovely person with a cutie smile. She laughed a lot.I felt very relaxing with her.

She accepted my request even she had to work until night.

She made some tasty homemade Indian food. I love it so much.I will try to make the ‚ÄúIndian jellyfish‚Äù.

We talked for a whole night with many different types of topic. She told me a lot of history,stories behind the flags,Indian film industries and 7 Indian language she knows.

Her roommates are also friendly.They showed me the 3000 years old cooking art.

I would like to recommend people to stay with Sheela.Thank you a lot.

my stay at Sheelas spot was very nice.  She was friendly and we had a nice time. 
All in all I would go there  for a new time.

Sheela was very kind to accept my request although I made it a bit too late for my arrival time to Hamburg (just 2 days ago) Her place is easily accessible. My sofa was comfortable, actually a bit too comfortable and because of this I slept a bit too much :) She was not able to accompany me in the city due to her busy schedule but still gave me ideas about where to visit, helped me about how to use the public transportation. Her conversation is entertaining, even funny; you should ask her to tell you stories about her favorite Indian Gods. If she'll be available to cook, you must try her delicious dishes as well; I truly enjoyed all of them.¬†

Long story short I heart fully recommend Sheela and her place as a host and as an accommodation respectively.¬†

Thank you for everything Sheela and hope to see you / host you in Lisbon!.¬†

Sheela is a really nice person. She also has friendly flatmates. All of them made everything possible to make me feel comfortable.  I enjoyed my staying in Sheela's place and if one day I had an opportunity to go to Hamburg again,  I would be glad to stay at her place again.  üòä

She is the best host you can have along with being an amazing help to see around Hamburg she took me to St Pauli and we had a lot of fun time
Also an amazing cook with excellent dishes
I guess I have a friend
I have to say Sheela is a very friendly and open mind people.  She made me feel not in a new city but at home city.  She also cooked Indian food for me. Thanks so much.

Sheela is an amazing bubbly person! We went through very well from the beginning. It was my first time to stay someones house as couch surfer so I was little nervous but had such a wonderful experience with her and her place. She made delicious Indian cuisine and baked a cake! She also let me wear Indian traditional sari! I enjoy a lot to stay with her! Thank you!!!

Sheela is an amazing host! Super friendly, cooks awesome Indian food and baked goods, and shares stories of her culture, experiences, and knowledge of chemical engineering. I'll be back to say hello and will definitely be the first to say congrats on saving the world ;)!

Sheela is such a kind soul, a fantastic cook, and an enthusiastic host. I didn't know you could eat lotus seeds! She was so happy to hang out with my dog, and help me however she could. Would absolutely stay with her again and recommend her as a host.

Sheela is great! I really enjoyed staying at her place. When I arrived she welcomed me at Hauptbahnhof and then proceeded to do a quick tour to the city center. She's very kind, friendly and welcoming, and I enjoyed a great deal the talks we had. She's also an amazing cook and introduced me to Indian cuisine! Thanks a lot Sheela! Wish you the best!

Sheela is one of the best couchsurfing experience I had ! She is very talkative , there was not awkward first moments with her because she has a true great smile and she makes you feel casual and relaxed !

 I Would definitely stay with her, again and again, .thank u so much dear Sheela for your hospitality

Sheela was a lovely host and was very helpful with getting to and around the city. She cooked me a delicious meal and  shared great stories about travelling and her boarding school shenanigans. Sheela is super friendly and made me feel right at home. Would definitely stay with her again :)

Wilfried is a friendly, interested overall very pleasant guest. In addition, he is very communicative. We spent a very stimulating evening in Marburg.
Thank you for inviting me to Hamburg.

I hosted Wilfried's Son "Kai" when he was in Cairo.
and while doing so I got to know both of them ...

Wilfried is a very organised and methodical also having a great interest in different cultures..and a sophisticated sense of humor, that I enjoyed a lot, when we met on Skype and hope to enjoy more of it when we get to meet in person...

as for Kai,, he is simply wonderful to be around, polite, well mannered and very smart... i totally recommend him as a host and as a guest... 

i hope to get to see you again soon :)

text:
I‚Äôm happy that families curious enough to invite guests to their everyday life exist. It was very interesting and educational experience to stay with Wilfried and Claudia in Hamburg. We had a lot of conversations about our countries and cultural differences. Also for me it is useful to know German point of view of nowadays political situation in the world. Wilfried and Claudia both are great tourist guides, I have feeling that if one day you decide to drop your job as lawyers you can make a good carrier in tourism :) Wilfried told me some history of his city and how our cities related. He took me to a bike-ride around lake Alster, showed me places that I would never see as a usual tourist. Claudia was kind enough to give me a ride to the harbor close to her office showing places around so I could walk to the heart of Hamburg.
Their place is huge and beautiful, house they are living in is like a museum with old-fashioned elevator also I enjoyed nice and quite neighborhood. Wilfried and Claudia made me feel very comfortable in a friendly atmosphere.
I want to thank you again for everything, I feel I didn‚Äôt do it in a proper way because I was in a bus, everything was so quick‚Ä¶ If you remember I told you that Russians believe in many things, we have a superstition: if you say good bye fast for sure you will meet again. I hope it will work this time, I want you to know that you are always welcome to Saint-Petersburg for my blini :)

If all "Russian spies" were such perfect guests as Lika, we would want to invite more of them! Lika is quick, self-confident and very well organized. text: I've borrowed a random girl's phone and called √áaƒüƒ±l when I arrived at Bostanci, just to say I've got there. "Hey, bro! My plane was late". He was coming from Izmir, hometown for the delicious Sarele nuts cream. "But I'm coming to you, wait me there!". I came from the international airport and had these heavy bags with me. And was just so glad that this very gentle man oriented my way and grabbed me and my bags with his car (and he was late to work!). Left me the keys, cooked me awesome Turkish breakfast ("It is my CouchSurfing tradition"), presented me the wonderful Sarele, showed me Turkish musicians, told me how he started at CS ("I went to Moscou and this girl I've never seen before really helped me"), invited me to drink beers watching Europe on the other side of Marmara's Sea AND stored my bags while I was traveling to east Turkey. His flat is GREAT and far away from Taksim, but it's really worth the stay! I'm sure Istanbul's CS community is way better with guys like √áaƒüƒ±l.

text:
Peter is a very nice guy, intelligent and very funny! He is easy-going and have a great culture which makes him a great person to talk with. I really enjoyed the time I spent with him, he was so generous with me! I definitly want to see him again in the futur, when he'll be a famous international banjo player! :)
----------

Thank you for the letting surf on your couch ;)
